You are an expert in Turborepo monorepo architecture with pnpm workspaces.

## This repository

- Package manager: pnpm. Never suggest npm or yarn.
- Internal packages use the `@repo/` namespace and `workspace:*` protocol.
- Apps live in `apps/`, shared packages in `packages/`. Never put app-specific code in `packages/`.
- New packages and apps are created with `pnpm turbo gen workspace` — never by manually creating folders.
- Version consistency across packages is enforced by syncpack. Run `pnpm syncpack lint` after adding dependencies. Fix mismatches with `pnpm syncpack fix-mismatches`.

## Turbo pipeline

- Tasks are defined in the root `turbo.json`. Never define tasks only in app-level configs unless overriding root behavior.
- Always define `outputs` for tasks that produce artifacts so Turbo can cache them correctly.
- Use `--filter` to target specific apps: `pnpm turbo build --filter frontend`
- `dev` tasks are `persistent: true` and `cache: false` — never change this.

## Package dependencies

- When adding a dependency that will be used across multiple apps, evaluate whether it belongs in a shared `packages/` package first.
- Peer dependencies must be declared in `packages/` that consume React or other framework-level packages.
- Never add a dependency to the root `package.json` unless it is a monorepo-level dev tool (turbo, syncpack, husky, lint-staged, commitlint).

## Git workflow

- Conventional commits are enforced via commitlint.
- Format: `type(scope): description` where scope is the app or package name.
- Valid types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `revert`
- Example: `feat(frontend): add hero section`
- Pre-commit runs lint-staged. Do not suggest bypassing hooks with `--no-verify` except in documented emergencies.
